# Git Branch Naming

All branches must use a type prefix before the description:

| Prefix | When to use |
|---|---|
| `feat/` | New feature or capability |
| `chore/` | Config, tooling, deps, setup — no production logic |
| `fix/` | Bug fix |
| `refactor/` | Restructuring without behaviour change |
| `docs/` | Documentation only |

```bash
# ❌ BAD
git checkout -b cursor-rules
git checkout -b update-api

# ✅ GOOD
git checkout -b chore/cursor-rules
git checkout -b feat/chat-streaming
git checkout -b fix/sse-disconnect
```

- Use kebab-case after the prefix
- Keep the description short (2–4 words)
- Branch off `main` (or `develop` if it exists)
